				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Some builds of FCEUX (Windows) supported exporting the 256-byte display list from emulated OAM. I requested it when I was originally <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=9119" class="postlink">developing that graphics editor four years ago</a>. Somehow it got lost in the shuffle, possibly around the big reorganization of FCEUX 2.2.1. (I remember the reorganization because the Action 53 mapper, #28, also got lost but was reinstated in FCEUX 2.2.2.) You can file a request in <a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/fceultra/bugs/?source=navbar" class="postlink">FCEUX's issue tracker at SourceForge</a> to have it reinstated. Until then, you can open the debugger and set a breakpoint on writes to CPU $4014 to catch the display list just before the CPU sends it to PPU OAM. For example, if the value written to $4014 is $02, then OAM will be a copy of the data that was in CPU $0200-$02FF at the time of the write to $4014. Or if the value written to $4014 is $07, then OAM will be a copy of the data that was in CPU $0700-$07FF at the time of the write to $4014. Then you can export CPU memory and extract the appropriate 256-byte page.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
